Comedy series by Simon Brett following the fortunes of three fortysomething sisters.

Simon Brett followed the successful After Henry with another middle-class sitcom about the lives of three women, in this case a family of sisters: Anna, Victoria and Charlotte .  The humour is gentle, and arises from the contrast between Anna, the self-assured and contented sibling, who spent her middle years caring for the trio's parents, and her two younger sisters, Victoria and Charlotte, one of whom is a neurotic, domineering housewife and the other a hystrionic with an incredibly messy love life. Both sisters regard Anna as the unfortunate of the family, but are in fact reliant on her support.
